Egyptian Stocks: Citadel Capital and Orascom Construction

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-07-20T11:07:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/egyptian-stocks-citadel-capital-and-orascom-construction.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
advanced for the first time in three days, increasing 0.3
percent to 5,158.3 at 12:57 p.m. in Cairo.  The following shares rose or fell. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Citadel Capital SAE (CCAP EY) rose as much as 2.5 percent
before trading 0.6 percent higher at 5.18 Egyptian pounds. The
Cairo-based private equity firm said its African railway unit
reported earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and
amortization of $674,000 for June. It also received approval for
a $40 million loan from  African Development Bank .  Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC)   advanced for the
first time in three days, gaining 1.3 percent to 270.06 pounds.
The Arab country’s biggest publicly traded builder said its
board of directors approved buying back about 675,000 shares
from July 26 to Aug. 25.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  